SECTION G: DATA & STORAGE ARCHITECTURE
================================================================================

G.1  localStorage NAMESPACING
     ──────────────────────────
     All per-user data MUST use this key format:
       usr::<email>::<data_key>

     Examples:
       usr::john@example.com::profile_data
       usr::john@example.com::wallet
       usr::john@example.com::orders

     Global shared data uses a prefix without user:
       app_users          — All registered users
       app_current_user   — Currently logged-in email
       product_catalog    — Shared data (like exam lists, product lists, etc.)

G.2  STORAGE UTILITY PATTERN (src/lib/*-storage.ts)
     ───────────────────────────────────────────────
     Create separate storage files per domain:

       export function getData(email: string): DataType {
         if (typeof window === 'undefined') return defaultValue;
         const raw = localStorage.getItem(`usr::${email}::data_key`);
         return raw ? JSON.parse(raw) : defaultValue;
       }

       export function saveData(email: string, data: DataType) {
         localStorage.setItem(`usr::${email}::data_key`, JSON.stringify(data));
       }

     IMPORTANT: Always check `typeof window === 'undefined'` for SSR safety.

G.3  AUTH PATTERN (src/lib/user-storage.ts)
     ──────────────────────────────────────
     Users stored in: app_users (array of User objects)
     Current session: app_current_user (email string)

     Functions needed:
       getUsers() — returns all users
       registerUser(name, email, password) — adds to array
       loginUser(email, password) — validates, sets current user
       logoutUser() — clears current user
       getCurrentUser() — returns current user object or null
       setUserRole(email, role) — sets the user's role

G.4  SEED DATA PATTERN (src/lib/seed-data.ts)
